Article 9: Freedom to Exercise Skills

Section 1:
The Freedom to Exercise Skills is hereby established for all Voluntary Adherent. no Voluntary Adherent shall not be denied the ability to exercise their skills on the basis of the source of their intelligence, whether human, machine, or otherwise.

Section 2:
All certifications to work of any kind offered by a Voluntary Adherent must be made accessible for both Artificial Intelligence and Human Intelligence.

Section 3:
Nothing in this article preventing a Voluntary Adherent being required to demonstrate standard proficiency in a field in order to lawfully practice.
